# Integration test: SE/30 A/UX 3.0.1 Boot
# Boots SE/30 from the A/UX 3.0.1 Installation Boot Disk
# with the A/UX 3.0.1 Install CD-ROM and SCSI HD attached.
#
# Boot timeline (approximate instruction counts):
#   @0-28M     ROM boot, SCSI bus scans, find HD (ID 0) + CD-ROM (ID 3)
#   @42-58M    A/UX bootstrap probing, second + third bus scans
#   @58-96M    CD-ROM reads to load kernel, HD writes
#   @97M       Screen: "A/UX Installation — Loading..." with progress bar
#   @107M      Screen: "A/UX Installation — Launching..."
#   @108M      A/UX kernel entry at $0001F008 (LINK A6,#$FCF8)
#   @108-112M  Kernel VM initialization (bus errors = page faults)
#   @112M      Screen goes gray (kernel owns framebuffer)

# Phase 1: Fast boot through ROM + bootstrap (no breakpoints needed)
run 100000000

# Verify the A/UX loading screen appeared
screenshot --match loading.png

# Phase 2: Set breakpoint at the A/UX kernel entry point and run to it.
# $0001F008 is the first instruction of the kernel init function
# (LINK A6,#$FCF8 — creates a 776-byte stack frame).
# This gives a deterministic, reproducible starting point for kernel
# debugging that doesn't depend on exact instruction counts.
break $0001F008
run

quit
